		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.50]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>You have some good points :&gt;<br><br>I have to take issue with one of your premises, though, even though what you speak of is common practice.<br><br>Anyway, in a group that has someone who can snare, (and that's you, if need be, once you get Bonds of Force), it makes much more sense NOT to go for the kill shot in most cases. (Mobs that don't flee when they are low on hp are the exception).<br><br>Why? Because you waste mana in 2 ways.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, when you get the kill shot, you might be nuking for 663 points of damage on a mob that only has 400 hp left.  Save your mana for when each of those 663 points of damage will count. Your tanks are better suited to finish that mob off.  Secondly, if snared and in "flee" mode, the mob is just standing there while your tanks beat on it.  The mob is not attacking.  Why waste mana? Let the tanks finish it so you can save your mana for when you need it.<br><br>Instead of aiming for the kill shot, try to nuke the mob so that you put it in "flee" mode.  The mob dies quicker that way.  Think about it.  If a mob has 2k hp at full health, and you go for the kill shot, doing 663 when the mob only has 400 hp left, you have left your tanks to do 1600 points of damage.  BUT, if you put it in "flee" mode instead of getting the kill shot, you do a full 663 points of damage, meaning your tanks need to do only 1337 points of damage.<br><br>Of course, all this changes if you don't have snare ;&gt;<br><br>Terrel Doom<br>Wizard of Veeshan</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
